canonical:
  title: 丙寅三月病後題
  author: 權思復
  language: lzh
  text: 病與年深生事微不知日去况春歸落花飛入軒窓裏始覺枝頭紅自稀
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 丙寅三月病後題
  author: 權思復
  language: lzh
  text: 病與年深生事微。不知日去况春歸。落花飛入軒窓裏。始覺枝頭紅自稀。
korean:
  title: 병인삼월병후제
  author: 권사복
  language: kor
  text: |-
    해를 따라 병 깊어 가매 사는 일이 귀찮구나
    날 가는 줄 모르거니 봄이 돌아감이랴
    지는 꽃이 창 안에 날아 드나니
    비로소 가지 끝이 성김을 깨닫겠네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0240_010_1180&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Written After Illness in the Third Month of the Year of Byungyin
  author: Gwon Sa-bok
  language: eng
  text: |-
    As illness deepens with the years, the affairs of living grow weary.
    Unaware that days slip away—how then should I notice spring's return?
    Falling petals drift through the window frame,
    And only then do I perceive the thinning blooms upon the branch.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: Byungyin (丙寅) refers to a year in the traditional East Asian sexagenary cycle, likely indicating a specific historical moment in the author's life. The poem reflects on how chronic illness obscures one's awareness of time's passage and the seasons' turning.
